snippet.textDisplay: My go to foods in a nightmarket in Wuchi were roasted butterflied squid with sesame seeds, spicy fried chicken wings, boiled catfish with sweet soy dipping sauce and fried octopus tentacles. My favorite breakfast items were egg pancakes and zongzi (glutinous rice stuffed with different fillings wrapped in lotus leaves). We also have a go to place if we want good chow mein and chow fan in Wuchi. If we want to eat sizzling steak and noodles, we have to go to Shalu. We go to Taichung city if we wanted to eat something fancier or if we wanted to shop. I can't believe that it's been 20 years since I've been in Taiwan but it was a good experience being there.
